t_ar":"عَارِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a loan"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) It is said in the story of the [golden] calf,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw A_isoraAy^iyla","text_ar":"بَنُو اـِسْرَايِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino HaloYK taEaw~arahu","text_ar":"مِنْ حَلْىٍ تَعَوَّرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaEaAruwhu","text_ar":"اِسْتَعَارُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of ornaments which the children of Israel had asked to be lent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had borrowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  You say also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaEarotu minohu Al$~aYo'a faA^aEaAraniyhi","text_ar":"اِسْتَعَرْتُ مِنْهُ الشَّىْءَ فَاَعَارَنِيهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K, *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaEarotuhu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"اِسْتَعَرْتُهُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, TA,) suppressing the preposition, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I asked of him the loan of the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and he lent it to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaEarotu minohu EaAriy~apF faA^aEaAraniyhaA","text_ar":"اِسْتَعَرْتُ مِنْهُ عَارِيَّةً فَاَعَارَنِيهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I asked of him a loan and he lent it to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaEaArahu vawobFA","text_ar":"اِسْتَعَارَهُ ثَوْبًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAhu","text_ar":"اـِيَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^aEaArahu","text_ar":"فَاَعَارَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He asked him to lend to him a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, and he lent it to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstEAr sahomFA mino kinaAnatihi","text_ar":"استعار سَهْمًا مِنْ كِنَانَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He raised and transferred an arrow from his quiver."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewr","text_ar":"عور"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstEAr lafoZFA","text_ar":"استعار لَفْظًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He used a word metaphorically."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["O","K","Mgh","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"استعارة","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22833#2e4175","body_html":"<span>الاستعارة: ادعاء معنى الحقيقة في الشيء للمبالغة في التشبيه، مع طرح ذكر المشبه من البين، كقولك: لقيت أسدًا، وأنت تعني به الرجل الشجاع، ثم إذا ذكر المشبه به مع ذكر القرينة يسمى: استعارة تصريحية وتحقيقية، نحو: لقيت أسدًا في الحمام، وإذا قلنا: المنية، أي الموت، أنشبت، أي علقت أظفارها بفلان، فقد شبهنا المنية بالسبع في اغتيال النفوس، أي إهلاكها، من غير تفرقة بين نفاع وضرار، فأثبتنا لها الأظافر، التي لا يكمل ذلك الاغتيال فيه بدونها؛ تحقيقًا للمبالغة في التشبيه، فتشبيه المنية بالسبع استعارة بالكناية، وإثبات الأظافر لها استعارة تخييلية. والاستعارة في الفعل لا تكون إلا تبعية، كنطقت الحال. </span>"}]}}